documentation: https://docs.python.org/3/reference/index.html
tutorial: https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/index.html

type python in cmd to start python 

in other languages data type must be declared initially. Python is dynamically typed language, teh data type of the variables is not required to be explicitly defind. 
They python interpreter implicitly binds the value fo the variable with its type at runtime. 

type function can be used to check the data type in python 

var = 13.2
print(var) will be float

print(type(var))
var = "Now the type is string"
print(type(var)) will be string 


print (type(12+31j)) is complex 


Principal Built in types: 
Numeric types: Integer (int), float, complex
Boolean types: bool 
Sequence types: String(str), range, list, tuple
Mapping types: dictionary (dict)
Set types: set, frozenset


in python booleans 0 is false, and any other number is true 

print(type(bool(22))) # <class 'bool'>
print(type(True)) # <class 'bool'>
print(type(False)) # <class 'bool'>

print(bool(False)) #False
print(bool(0)) #False
print(bool(11)) #True 
print(bool(-2.3)) #True 




